cs.CL, cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI

This paper focuses on the use of word embeddings for malicious spelling correction, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also deals with cybersecurity and detection of malicious content, which suggests categories such as cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of machine learning techniques for spelling correction and detection also suggests categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
